<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Public Affairs Select Committee Enquiry on Crime statistics</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Written Evidence from the Sussex Police Crime Commissioner [CST0014]</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Interpretation of the counting rules is subject to much meaningful debate locally, regionally and nationally.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">We have therefore six apparently simple questions that require technically complex </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">decisions.  A</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">s the force crime registrar for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Sussex</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> I </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">attend regional</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> and national meeting</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> where issues are discussed with a view to providing clarification by means of examples for inclusion in the counting rules.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Each incident has to be judged on its o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">wn merits </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">hence m</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">y response therefore is global</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> rather than local</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> in an attempt </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">highlight </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">daily debates/issues that impact on recorded crime figures.   </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">1.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Are crimes being recorded by the police when they should be? Are crimes being categorised </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">correctly?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">An interesting opening question as nothing is ever straight forward particularly given the subjective judgements when interpreting the counting rules</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.  Influencing factors, in no particular order include, but are not restricted to:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 9.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Under willi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ngness</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> to criminalise</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 9.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Under the age of criminal responsibility </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 9.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Interpretation of “Reasonably assumed to be acting on behalf of”</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 9.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Not considered to be actually reporting a crime - just want </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">p</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">olice to give words of advice.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 9.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Officer discretion all to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> often in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">terpreted to mean “incident dealt with</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> therefore Counting Rules don’t apply - no need to record a crime” </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 9.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Balance of probability</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 9.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Credible evidence to contrary requirement ignored</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 9.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Case Law used as means to justify not </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">criming</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 9.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Not considered to have </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">m</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ens</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">r</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ea</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 9.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Previous allegations used as reason for not recording as opposed to treating every incident on its own merits.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 9.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">A lack of evidence of a crime is NOT evidence of a lack of a crime.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 9.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Allegation of harassment - Issues around course of conduct complete - </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">i.e. this is the first time police informed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> rather than the number of times the aggrieved has been subject to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">such behaviour</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.34pt; padding-left:4.66pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">What are the factors which can influence police </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">mis</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">-recording of crime?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">The raison d’être of NCRS is to promote greater consistency between police forces </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">in the recording of crime and to ensure a more victim focused approach.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Interpretation of NCRS and the counting rules</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> is however subjective and the topic of much debate and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">discussion nationally on many occasions.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">The general principles of the NCRS rightly focus on a victim centric crime recording process.  In other words if a victim makes an allegation that amounts to an offence in law which is contained within the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">notifiab</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">le</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> crime series</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> then such a crime should be recorded unless there is evidence to contradict that which is alleged.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 9.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Mixed messages from central government / Home Office / ACPO in so far as HOCR </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">are considered fit for purpose but still they are questione</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">d</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 9.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">The suggestion “</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">lets de-clutter</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> the counting rules”</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> (the clutter is the conduit for achieving a level playing field</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, supports compliance and encourages data integrity</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 9.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Irrespective of any National /Force statements to the contrary “Performance Targets” </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">still exist and are pursued with vigour</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">  Example from F</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">orce </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">rime </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">R</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">egistrqars</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> national meeting</span></li><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 25.2pt; padding-left:7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Mother contacts police stating son/daughter (age 11 / 12 ) has taken minimum amount of money from her purse - whilst </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">its</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> easy to jump to the conclusion all tha</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">t’s required is “words of advice” - </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">don’t crime/criminalise interpretation goes against HOCR/level playing field.  </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 25.2pt; padding-left:7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Is this </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">example</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> more to do with the amount of money (if so at what amount would the decision be to record a crime?  Or is it to do with </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">the age of the child (if so at what age would a crime be recorded?  (HOCR requires a crime is recorded even if child is under age of criminal responsibility (age 10) as HOCR are victim focused) </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 25.2pt; padding-left:7pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">The integrity of recorded crime figures would be open to sign</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ificant challenge if forces had to interpret whether “victims” were actually reporting a crime or not.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span></li></ul><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 9.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Counting Rules and Charging S</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">tandards differ.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.34pt; padding-left:4.66pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Are the right checks in place to ensure that the systems for recording crime function effectively and acc</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">urately?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">In the current financial climate</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> the cost of any “back office” support function has to be balanced against operational</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> requirements.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-famil